  "text": "We will follow the conventions of [CITATION_1] . The STU model is the four-dimensional ungauged N = 2 supergravity coupled to 3 vector multiplets with cubic prepotential F = −X 1 X 2 X 3 /X 0 . This model occurs as a consistent truncation of various supergravity theories. The bosonic content of the action is the metric, four gauge fields A I µ , I = 1, 2, 3, 4, and three complex scalar fields z i = x i + iy i = χ i + ie −ϕ i , i = 1, 2, 3. The U-duality group of this supergravity is SL(2, R) 3 together with the finite group of permutations of three elements. This group is usually called the triality U-duality group or triality group in short.",
